# .trivyignore — CVEs accepted as upstream-only or false positives.
#
# Each line is a CVE ID. Add a comment above explaining why.
# Review this file when upgrading the base image (python:3.14-slim).
#
# Format:
#   # reason for ignoring
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN

# Perl CVEs — nfr-review never invokes Perl; these are transitive
# dependencies of the Debian base image with no available fixes.
CVE-2026-42496
CVE-2026-8376
CVE-2026-48962
CVE-2026-42497
CVE-2026-9538

# Python 3.13 / expat — only exploitable when parsing untrusted XML.
# nfr-review does not parse XML from untrusted sources. Fix deferred by Debian.
CVE-2026-7210

# xdg-utils — CLI tool used for mailto: URIs. Not used at runtime.
CVE-2022-4055

# gh (Go stdlib) — bundled for CI convenience, not used at runtime.
# Fixed in gh 1.26.4; will clear on next base-image rebuild.
CVE-2026-42504
